136
00:09:32,739 --> 00:09:35,117
Doreen, after all these years,
after everything we've been through,

137
00:09:35,283 --> 00:09:36,963
are you still refusing to call me Richard?

138
00:09:36,993 --> 00:09:41,089
Yes! Now, you have a ten o'clock meeting
with the new owners.

139
00:09:41,289 --> 00:09:43,257
- Yeah.
- Any idea who they are?

140
00:09:43,416 --> 00:09:44,416
Hmm...

141
00:09:45,668 --> 00:09:47,966
Young is all I know, Doreen.

142
00:09:48,129 --> 00:09:50,302
I took your advice
on their pension share offer.

143
00:09:50,465 --> 00:09:52,433
- I took them up on it.
- What? The whole lot?

144
00:09:52,592 --> 00:09:56,722
Yes, lots of us did.
Janice in Accounts, Marcus in Payroll.

145
00:09:56,930 --> 00:09:59,024
Well, it's a solid offer.

146
00:09:59,182 --> 00:10:02,732
Now, you have a prostate check
at 2:15 today.

147
00:10:03,978 --> 00:10:05,946
I'm gonna miss these little chats, Doreen.

148
00:10:13,154 --> 00:10:15,452
I thought my leaving party
was on Friday.

149
00:10:15,615 --> 00:10:18,084
I don't think this is a party, Mr Jones.

150
00:10:18,243 --> 00:10:21,042
- It's all gone, Richard. The lot!
- What?

151
00:10:23,248 --> 00:10:24,716
Morning, everyone.

152
00:10:32,173 --> 00:10:34,426
Richard, what's going on?

153
00:10:34,592 --> 00:10:36,265
I don't know, Janice.
I have no idea.

154
00:10:36,427 --> 00:10:38,270
- Did you know about this?
- No, of course not, Marcus.

155
00:10:38,429 --> 00:10:41,029
- Is this legal? Can they just do this?
- Yes, of course they can.

156
00:10:41,057 --> 00:10:42,900
Now, wait a minute.
We don't know that.

157
00:10:43,059 --> 00:10:45,061
Just... just give me
some time here, please.

158
00:10:45,228 --> 00:10:46,855
- Will we get paid this month?
- Yes, of course you will.

159
00:10:47,021 --> 00:10:49,365
- Did you know this was coming?
- Of course he didn't!

160
00:10:49,524 --> 00:10:51,777
Someone said the shares are worthless.
Is that true?

161
00:10:51,943 --> 00:10:53,320
- No.
- Yes.

162
00:10:58,324 --> 00:11:00,122
Jesus!

163
00:11:00,285 --> 00:11:05,416
I suppose they'll let us in at some point.
To collect our things, I mean.

164
00:11:05,582 --> 00:11:08,882
Doreen, I promise you,
I will sort this out.

165
00:11:14,257 --> 00:11:17,352
Everyone, listen up! I promise you
I'll get to the bottom of this.

166
00:11:17,510 --> 00:11:20,309
I will find out what's going on
but I just need some time, OK?

167
00:11:20,430 --> 00:11:21,807
What are we supposed to do now?

168
00:11:21,973 --> 00:11:24,772
- How?
- But, Richard, what can you do?

169
00:11:24,934 --> 00:11:27,653
<i>I...</i> I don't know, but I promise you,

170
00:11:27,812 --> 00:11:31,487
I will make sure that every one of you
gets what they're due.

171
00:11:31,649 --> 00:11:35,870
I will not, will not, let you down.

172
00:11:44,871 --> 00:11:47,966
OK, Jean-Baptiste, here I come.

173
00:11:49,626 --> 00:11:53,597
I am interested in the, er...

174
00:11:53,755 --> 00:11:57,760
...the arts and culture.

175
00:11:58,468 --> 00:12:03,269
I love travel and adventure

176
00:12:03,431 --> 00:12:06,981
and generally being...

177
00:12:07,143 --> 00:12:12,445
...spon-tan-eous.

178
00:12:12,565 --> 00:12:13,782
Whoosh!

179
00:12:15,235 --> 00:12:16,953
