182
00:12:27,914 --> 00:12:28,710
Blimey!

183
00:12:28,873 --> 00:12:33,174
'Known in the trade as the Eye of the Rainbow
because of its distinctive colouring in the light

184
00:12:33,336 --> 00:12:38,058
"it was bought at auction in New York.
Today's buyer wishes to remain anonymous.

185
00:12:38,216 --> 00:12:40,469
'However, Sotheby's <i>says</i> the buyer plans...

186
00:12:40,593 --> 00:12:43,016
'...for the stone
to be the centrepiece of a necklace...

187
00:12:43,179 --> 00:12:44,619
Or to be sold for starving children.

188
00:12:44,681 --> 00:12:46,103
'...for one lucky lady likely
to be extremely happy

189
00:12:46,266 --> 00:12:48,985
'with her gift this evening.

190
00:12:49,143 --> 00:12:51,020
"Coming up on Sky News at seven...'

191
00:12:51,187 --> 00:12:52,609
Oh, bloody hell!

192
00:12:52,772 --> 00:12:53,989
OK.

193
00:12:55,858 --> 00:12:57,906
Ken, I'm coming for you.

194
00:13:00,738 --> 00:13:03,332
Oh, twice in one week.
What have I done to deserve this?

195
00:13:03,491 --> 00:13:05,611
- Kate, we need to talk.
- Not now, Richard. I'm busy.

196
00:13:05,660 --> 00:13:06,582
- Please, I just need to...
- Hello!

197
00:13:06,744 --> 00:13:08,872
- Hello, Ken.
- Look, no flowers!

198
00:13:09,038 --> 00:13:10,335
Well done!

199
00:13:11,165 --> 00:13:14,669
- Oh, it's you again.
- Ken. Again, hi.

200
00:13:14,836 --> 00:13:17,305
Kate, I need to speak to you.

201
00:13:17,463 --> 00:13:18,760
- I'll see you...
- Yes...

202
00:13:19,924 --> 00:13:22,848
OK, great.
Looking forward.

203
00:13:24,721 --> 00:13:27,270
- Have you been drinking?
- No... Yes.

204
00:13:27,432 --> 00:13:29,792
- Look, what difference does it make?
- A lot of difference.

205
00:13:29,809 --> 00:13:32,733
You're prone to exaggeration
and wild statements of intent.

206
00:13:32,854 --> 00:13:34,697
Look, there are big problems at the office.

207
00:13:34,856 --> 00:13:38,201
Please, tell it to Anastasia or Michaela
or whoever the latest is...

208
00:13:38,359 --> 00:13:40,487
Culco has gone into receivership.

209
00:13:40,653 --> 00:13:43,623
The new owners have stripped us
of any value and run us into the ground.

210
00:13:43,781 --> 00:13:44,781
The shares are worthless.

211
00:13:44,907 --> 00:13:47,410
My pension, your pension,
was all tied up in those shares.

212
00:13:47,577 --> 00:13:50,501
The mortgage payments on my place,
this place, the kids' university fees,

213
00:13:50,663 --> 00:13:53,587
everything we'd saved up for
them afterwards, it's all gone.

214
00:13:54,208 --> 00:13:57,508
Kate, I virtually had
the whole company on board.

215
00:13:57,670 --> 00:14:00,799
Marcus, Janice,
I even got Doreen involved.

216
00:14:03,926 --> 00:14:05,894
Come on.

217
00:14:06,054 --> 00:14:07,334
What do we know
about these guys?

218
00:14:07,388 --> 00:14:10,483
Lavco. They came in hard and fast
out of nowhere.

219
00:14:10,641 --> 00:14:12,860
The holding company
traded by the name of Lexon.

220
00:14:13,019 --> 00:14:16,614
We were persuaded
to integrate our pension fund into theirs.

221
00:14:16,773 --> 00:14:19,151
Turns out Lexon was hollow, toxic.

222
00:14:19,317 --> 00:14:23,072
So when they turned to dust,
so did our pension.

223
00:14:23,237 --> 00:14:25,911
There's always someone bigger
behind these things,

224
00:14:26,074 --> 00:14:29,123
someone who manages
to wipe their hands clean and move on.

225
00:14:33,289 --> 00:14:35,417
- Still allergic to cat hair?
- Worse than ever.

226
00:14:35,583 --> 00:14:37,756
Go on, Rumpy, sit on him.

227
00:14:38,336 --> 00:14:40,134
- I see you got your PhD.
- Yeah.

228
00:14:40,296 --> 00:14:44,517
- So, how's life as a lecturer?
- Under-paid.

229
00:14:44,717 --> 00:14:47,470
- What are the students like?
- Under-motivated.

230
00:14:47,637 --> 00:14:50,607
Could you just stop fidgeting
and sit down?

231
00:14:50,765 --> 00:14:54,736
I'm on the site but I can't get
any real info. I'm being blocked.

232
00:14:54,894 --> 00:14:57,067
We need a password.

233
00:14:57,230 --> 00:14:59,449
- We need...
- Matt.

234
00:14:59,607 --> 00:15:00,654
We need Matt.

235
00:15:00,817 --> 00:15:02,615
'Mum, you do know hacking is illegal.'

236
00:15:02,777 --> 00:15:05,297
'I know, Matt and I would never want you
to do anything illegal.

237
00:15:05,321 --> 00:15:09,872
'But I wondered if you could just...
accidentally stumble into it.'

