00:46:12,395 --> 00:46:14,523
Contacts? No, Jerry we don't.

708
00:46:14,689 --> 00:46:18,990
Well, if you must know, I once
had a brief, er... affair of the heart

709
00:46:19,151 --> 00:46:20,619
with a young jewellery designer.

710
00:46:20,778 --> 00:46:24,658
Affair of the heart
with a young jewellery designer!

711
00:46:24,824 --> 00:46:26,121
Calm down, Pen.
It's all right.

712
00:46:26,284 --> 00:46:28,965
Yeah, don't worry, Pen.
It's all in the past, all forgotten.

713
00:46:29,453 --> 00:46:31,706
This is the basic layout of the chéteau.

714
00:46:31,872 --> 00:46:33,874
Do you know
where all the guards might be?

715
00:46:34,000 --> 00:46:36,423
Yeah, yeah, yeah.
Absolutely, yes.

716
00:46:36,585 --> 00:46:38,553
- No Jerry?
- No.

717
00:46:38,713 --> 00:46:40,193
Rushed off while I was having a bath.

718
00:46:40,298 --> 00:46:44,144
Said he had to meet a man about something.
Very odd, the whole thing.

719
00:46:44,302 --> 00:46:46,475
Anyway, don't let him spoil this.

720
00:46:46,637 --> 00:46:49,186
This is lovely, seeing the two of you
being back together.

721
00:46:49,307 --> 00:46:52,561
Sorry, everyone. Got held up.
Quick little mission.

722
00:46:53,311 --> 00:46:56,690
I was just saying this is lovely and it's
lovely to see our friends back together.

723
00:46:56,856 --> 00:46:59,530
- <i>Pen, can we get</i> back <i>to the plan?
- Absolument. Pardon.</i>

724
00:46:59,692 --> 00:47:02,320
Now, this is where
the guests will be making their entrance.

725
00:47:02,486 --> 00:47:04,566
And we will be required
to show our invitations here.

726
00:47:04,697 --> 00:47:07,166
Now, you are going to be the Baxters
and we will be the Hicks.

727
00:47:07,325 --> 00:47:10,124
- And actually, Matt... Cheers.
- Cheers, everyone.

728
00:47:10,286 --> 00:47:12,334
Matt has done some research
into each couple.

729
00:47:12,538 --> 00:47:14,006
- Hey! Your Matt?
- Our Matt.

730
00:47:14,165 --> 00:47:16,088
- Such a bright boy.
- Thank you.

731
00:47:16,250 --> 00:47:17,968
Not like our Tim, is he?

732
00:47:18,127 --> 00:47:19,925
- That's disloyal, Jerry.
- Well, I was just being honest.

733
00:47:20,087 --> 00:47:23,057
He's an academic disaster zone, isn't he?
Police tape all around him.

734
00:47:23,215 --> 00:47:24,341
Jerry!

735
00:47:24,550 --> 00:47:27,599
Now, we know that the bride will retire to
her bedroom at some point during the night

736
00:47:27,762 --> 00:47:30,356
to change her frock and the new frock
will be accompanied by the diamond.

737
00:47:30,514 --> 00:47:33,734
Now, hopefully, Richard and I
will have gained access through here.

738
00:47:33,893 --> 00:47:37,318
We'll attempt to swap out the diamond,
delivering the real one into your arms, Jerry.

739
00:47:37,521 --> 00:47:40,320
Now, you two will leave the party early
and if anything happens to us,

740
00:47:40,483 --> 00:47:42,483
if we get caught,
we're just a disgruntled employee

741
00:47:42,568 --> 00:47:43,740
and his pushy ex-wife

742
00:47:43,861 --> 00:47:45,861
who've had their pensions stolen
and won't go away.

743
00:47:45,905 --> 00:47:49,455
They'll find nothing on us
and they'll let us go.

744
00:47:49,617 --> 00:47:51,164
- Right.
- Or they'll kill us.

745
00:47:51,327 --> 00:47:52,954
Chop us up
and throw us in the Med.

746
00:47:53,162 --> 00:47:54,709
- Oh, God.
- Richard!

747
00:47:54,872 --> 00:47:57,716
It's out there. It's a possibility.

748
00:48:00,461 --> 00:48:03,965
Jerry, why do you keep winking at Richard
and patting your pocket?

749
00:48:04,131 --> 00:48:06,509
What? What are you talking about?
Nothing. I'm not doing anything.

750
00:48:06,717 --> 00:48:08,094
I know when you're lying.

751
00:48:08,260 --> 00:48:10,421
Get off me, woman. Whey-hey!
What are you doing, woman?

752
00:48:10,471 --> 00:48:13,065
- Hey! Ho-ho!
- God, he's got a gun!

753
00:48:14,058 --> 00:48:15,058
What?

754
00:48:15,184 --> 00:48:17,232
Don't advertise it
to the whole flipping restaurant!

755
00:48:17,395 --> 00:48:19,614
Why have you got a gun
and why have you brought it to dinner?

756
00:48:19,772 --> 00:48:21,319
<i>'</i> Are you crazy?
- Crazy? Me?

757
00:48:21,482 --> 00:48:25,328
- Kate, Richard, talk to him.
- Jerry, actually, why have you got a gun?

758
00:48:25,486 --> 00:48:29,366
It's a replica. Calm down. We just
thought it was a good idea, that's all.

759
00:48:29,532 --> 00:48:31,284
It's a real one, actually.
They didn't have any replicas left.

760
00:48:31,409 --> 00:48:34,583
- Bloody hell.
- We? So you're behind this brilliant plan?

761
00:48:34,745 --> 00:48:36,793
Richard, have you led Jerry astray?

762
00:48:36,956 --> 00:48:39,880
- What? No! It was his idea.
- Led me astray? I'm not a flipping child.

763
00:48:40,084 --> 00:48:41,336
They were my contacts.

764
00:48:41,502 --> 00:48:44,676
Jerry, where did you get this?
I demand to know!

765
00:48:44,839 --> 00:48:48,935
Well, it's someone I knew a long time ago.

766
00:48:49,093 --> 00:48:51,767
I was passing through France
on my way to Guam.

767
00:48:51,929 --> 00:48:54,728
How come I don't know anything about this?
I've been married to you for <i>35</i> years, Jerry.

768
00:48:54,890 --> 00:48:57,188
- You've completely spoiled the whole evening.
- All right, love.

769
00:48:57,351 --> 00:48:59,351
- Have some more wine.
- Just have a bit more wine.

770
00:49:00,855 --> 00:49:02,573
Let's at least see it, then.

771
00:49:02,731 --> 00:49:04,449
- Yeah, let's have a look.
- See what?

772
00:49:04,608 --> 00:49:07,077
- The gun, Jerry.
- What? You want to see it?

773
00:49:07,236 --> 00:49:09,534
- I do, actually.
- Let's have a look. Come on.

774
00:49:09,697 --> 00:49:11,540
- Come on, then.
- All right.

775
00:49:11,699 --> 00:49:14,543
- All right.
- Nobody's watching.

776
00:49:14,702 --> 00:49:17,662
Hey-hey! Have a look at that.
All right, all right. One at a time!

777
00:49:19,832 --> 00:49:21,630
Whoops, sorry.

778
00:49:22,460 --> 00:49:23,837
Oh!

779
00:49:29,425 --> 00:49:31,644
Freeze, you melon farmers.

780
00:49:31,802 --> 00:49:33,475
- Steady, Pen.
- Oh, sorry.

781
00:49:33,637 --> 00:49:34,637
Put it down.

782
00:49:35,806 --> 00:49:36,806
Jesus Christ!

783
00:49:38,851 --> 00:49:40,228
All right, er...

784
00:49:40,394 --> 00:49:42,271
- Out the door. Shall we?
- Yeah. Drink up.

785
00:49:42,438 --> 00:49:43,906
The bill, please.

786
00:49:44,064 --> 00:49:45,862
Well, that was something, wasn't it?

787
00:49:46,025 --> 00:49:47,993
- Do you'll think we'll get arrested?
- No.

788
00:49:48,152 --> 00:49:49,620
Oi, chaps, chaps.
Good news.

789
00:49:49,778 --> 00:49:52,657
I've just been talking to the owner.
Turns out we were in the Legion together.

790
00:49:52,823 --> 00:49:55,246
He says if we, er... pay for the wine,
everything's OK.

791
00:49:55,409 --> 00:49:57,286
- Fantastic.
- Oh, fabulous.

792
00:49:57,453 --> 00:50:01,424
- I feel a bit giddy, Jerry.
- Oh, I say! You all right there, Pen?

793
00:50:01,582 --> 00:50:03,710
- Bedtime for us all.
- Right-o.

794
00:50:03,876 --> 00:50:05,253
- Good night, then.
- Good night.

795
00:50:07,713 --> 00:50:11,809
- What are you doing?
- Well... they seem so happy.

796
00:50:11,967 --> 00:50:14,811
You know, with the idea of us.

797
00:50:14,970 --> 00:50:17,473
I don't want to spoil it
for them, that's all.

798
00:50:17,640 --> 00:50:20,894
<i>Just... oh... just...</i>

799
00:50:21,060 --> 00:50:22,528
Just...

800
00:50:22,728 --> 00:50:25,527
Oh... Oh!

801
00:50:25,689 --> 00:50:27,737
Oh, that feels good.

802
00:50:30,110 --> 00:50:32,909
Do you think we're doing the right thing?

803
00:50:33,948 --> 00:50:38,078
You know, diamond stealing and kidnapping.

804
00:50:38,244 --> 00:50:40,793
Without a shadow of a doubt.

805
00:50:43,040 --> 00:50:45,008
Sit down for a minute.

806
00:50:54,426 --> 00:50:56,394
I said sit.

807
00:50:59,473 --> 00:51:01,567
Lying down is fine too.

808
00:51:02,560 --> 00:51:05,234
Pen and I had a gin, doubles.

809
00:51:05,396 --> 00:51:08,650
I just can't take it. I can't take
my booze anymore. That's the thing.

810
00:51:08,816 --> 00:51:12,662
Well... it just whips my arse.

811
00:51:13,195 --> 00:51:15,914
You're much more likeable
these days, you know?

812
00:51:16,073 --> 00:51:18,542
That's nice. Thanks.

813
00:51:20,244 --> 00:51:22,042
So are you.

814
00:51:23,247 --> 00:51:26,046
We were much too young when we met.

815
00:51:28,127 --> 00:51:30,926
We should have met now instead.

816
00:51:33,757 --> 00:51:36,556
I don't think it works like that.

817
00:51:39,013 --> 00:51:40,481
Why not?

818
00:51:45,394 --> 00:51:49,444
Why did the latest one leave you?

819
00:51:53,611 --> 00:51:55,238
She didn't, actually.

820
00:51:56,905 --> 00:51:58,873
I left her.

821
00:52:02,911 --> 00:52:04,254
Hmm.

822
00:52:06,582 --> 00:52:08,710
- How's your back?
- Terrible.

823
00:52:08,876 --> 00:52:11,004
How's your bunions?

824
00:52:11,754 --> 00:52:13,882
Oh, excruciating.

825
00:52:15,924 --> 00:52:18,052
Sweet dreams.

826
00:52:19,094 --> 00:52:20,892
Night-night.

827
00:52:23,599 --> 00:52:25,067
Oh.

828
00:52:27,311 --> 00:52:30,360
- Oh, God! We didn't, did we?
- No.

829
00:52:30,522 --> 00:52:33,321
Oh! Thank God.

830
00:52:34,234 --> 00:52:36,202
You don't have to sound
so relieved about it.

831
00:52:41,492 --> 00:52:42,994
Oh.

832
00:52:44,745 --> 00:52:47,999
I haven't had sex for two years.
I'd like to have remembered it.

833
00:52:52,461 --> 00:52:56,136
Jerry, try this.
Please, cos it's so juicy. Go on.

834
00:52:56,298 --> 00:52:58,266
See what I mean?
Gorgeous.

835
00:52:58,425 --> 00:53:00,223
Hey, hey, hey, hey.
Here he is.

836
00:53:00,386 --> 00:53:01,433
- Hello.
- The stallion.

837
00:53:01,595 --> 00:53:04,018
Didn't get much sleep last night,
old son, did you?

838
00:53:04,181 --> 00:53:07,060
- Oh, Jerry.
- Oh, the old bed did shake, eh?

839
00:53:07,226 --> 00:53:09,854
- Only my snoring, Jerry. That's all it was.
- Right you are.

840
00:53:10,020 --> 00:53:12,899
Looks like we've got a bit of a problem.
Matt did some digging around last night.

841
00:53:13,065 --> 00:53:15,443
Apparently there are going to be
fingerprint sensors

842
00:53:15,567 --> 00:53:16,727
at the entrance to the party.

843
00:53:16,777 --> 00:53:19,155
Everyone's going to be scanned
before they're allowed in.

844
00:53:19,321 --> 00:53:21,699
- It's worse than Fort Knox.
- Mm-hmm.

845
00:53:21,907 --> 00:53:25,252
We could shave off their fingertips
and stick them onto ours.

846
00:53:26,286 --> 00:53:28,630
The Texans, I mean.
I saw it in a film once.

847
00:53:28,789 --> 00:53:30,712
- Pen...
- Oh, sorry.

848
00:53:30,916 --> 00:53:33,385
- I do get carried away.
- Good to think outside the box.

849
00:53:33,544 --> 00:53:35,546
We should go with something
a bit more mainstream, though.

850
00:53:35,713 --> 00:53:37,215
- Can everyone swim?
- Yes.

851
00:53:37,339 --> 00:53:39,558
- How about climbing?
- Have you ever climbed, Jerry?

852
00:53:39,717 --> 00:53:40,934
- He has not.
- Yeah, I have.

853
00:53:41,093 --> 00:53:42,436
- I have.
- Jerry! When?

854
00:53:42,594 --> 00:53:45,939
- When?
- I was in the Australian Parachute Regiment.

855
00:53:51,145 --> 00:53:52,442
7:28.

856
00:53:52,604 --> 00:53:54,151
- 7:32.
- 7:32.

857
00:53:54,314 --> 00:53:55,361
6:30.

858
00:53:55,524 --> 00:53:57,993
- Jerry, you're still on English time.
- Oh, yeah, of course.

859
00:53:58,152 --> 00:54:00,075
OK, let's do this.

860
00:54:57,544 --> 00:54:59,797
Jerry! Jerry!

861
00:54:59,963 --> 00:55:01,385
You're going the wrong way.

862
00:55:03,091 --> 00:55:04,468
Right you are.

863
00:55:36,792 --> 00:55:38,260
- Pen!
- Jerry!

864
00:55:38,418 --> 00:55:39,590
- Ow!
- Ow!

865
00:55:39,753 --> 00:55:41,050
What on earth are you doing?

866
00:55:42,005 --> 00:55:44,474
- Jerry!
- It's OK.

867
00:56:03,694 --> 00:56:05,162
- All right?
- Yeah.

868
00:56:07,865 --> 00:56:11,210
Oh... Oh, Jesus.

869
00:56:11,368 --> 00:56:13,996
You're scared of heights.
How could I forget? Are you all right?

870
00:56:14,872 --> 00:56:16,966
I'm fine, thank you.

871
00:56:17,124 --> 00:56:19,252
- Pen, you're squashing my head!
- Ssh, ssh!

872
00:56:19,418 --> 00:56:21,216
I'm sorry, darling.

873
00:56:30,804 --> 00:56:33,808
- Ssh, ssh, ssh!
- I've got you. I'm here.

874
00:56:33,974 --> 00:56:36,727
Well done, Jerry.

875
00:56:36,894 --> 00:56:38,362
Right.

876
00:56:38,854 --> 00:56:41,653
- Have you got the gun?
- No, sorry, Richard.

877
00:56:41,815 --> 00:56:44,193
I put my foot down.
I just decided it was too dangerous.

878
00:56:44,359 --> 00:56:46,532
- Quite right.
- I simply don't trust myself around it.

879
00:56:46,695 --> 00:56:49,073
But I made sandwiches, egg mayo.
Anyone hungry?

880
00:56:49,239 --> 00:56:51,662
- Oh, great, I'm starving.
- Pen, I think we should get on.

881
00:56:51,825 --> 00:56:53,623
Yeah, come on, this way.

882
00:56:53,785 --> 00:56:55,412
Stay close to me, Jerry.

883
00:57:24,107 --> 00:57:25,609
You look fine in that hat.

884
00:57:25,776 --> 00:57:27,949
Mr and Mrs Chambord, from Qatar.

885
00:57:28,153 --> 00:57:29,370
<i>- Bonsoir.
- Bonsoir.</i>

886
00:57:29,529 --> 00:57:31,577
Mr Chabert, from Bordeaux.

887
00:57:32,699 --> 00:57:35,669
Mr and Mrs Ossman, from Hanoi.

888
00:57:36,078 --> 00:57:38,239
- Congratulations.
- Merci.

889
00:57:38,246 --> 00:57:39,964
Thanks for coming.

890
00:57:40,123 --> 00:57:44,253
Mr and Mrs Hicks and Mr and Mrs Baxter
from Houston, Texas.

891
00:57:44,419 --> 00:57:46,513
- Ah, that's us!
- Hey! Bonsoir.

892
00:57:46,672 --> 00:57:49,050
<i>- So</i> glad you made it. Long way to come.
- Howdy partner!

893
00:57:49,216 --> 00:57:52,186
- Real great to be here.
- We'll find time to talk later. Welcome.

894
00:57:52,344 --> 00:57:54,472
Of course, this is not really a wedding.

895
00:57:54,638 --> 00:57:56,640
- It's a chance to do some business.
- Sweetheart.

896
00:57:56,807 --> 00:57:59,887
Well, you're not to bore us with all that
oil talk. I'm here to have some fun.

897
00:57:59,935 --> 00:58:03,485
Oh, we like fun, don't we?
Come along, missy.

898
00:58:03,647 --> 00:58:06,446
Thank you.
It's a mighty fine chéteau.

899
00:58:07,734 --> 00:58:09,987
Mr and Mrs Beltrami, from Rome.

900
00:58:14,950 --> 00:58:18,545
- I think that went quite well.
- For now.

901
00:58:19,162 --> 00:58:21,460
Let's blend in.

902
00:58:21,623 --> 00:58:25,002
Darling, I need to powder my nose.
Would you be so kind as to accompany me?

903
00:58:25,168 --> 00:58:27,136
- It would be my pleasure.
- Thank you.

904
00:58:27,295 --> 00:58:29,093
- Ey-up.
- Jerry!

905
00:58:29,256 --> 00:58:33,352
Merci. Well, Kate said
to blend in, didn't she?

906
00:58:33,510 --> 00:58:35,854
- Here's to us.
- Yeah.

907
00:58:41,435 --> 00:58:43,233
- Which floor?
- Second floor.

908
00:58:43,395 --> 00:58:44,863
Right.

909
00:58:46,773 --> 00:58:48,241
Right.

910
00:58:51,028 --> 00:58:52,826
Back in a tick.

911
00:59:20,348 --> 00:59:25,980
That's it, that's her room.
OK, Jerry. 30 seconds.

912
00:59:27,522 --> 00:59:30,196
Howdy, partner!
How ya doin' there?

913
00:59:30,358 --> 00:59:33,362
- Come on.
- I'm looking for the old John Wayne.

914
00:59:33,528 --> 00:59:39,160
The, er... pissoir, the, er... bog crapper?
Any idea?

915
00:59:39,326 --> 00:59:41,795
Sorry, sir, downstairs.
This ﬂoor is private.

916
00:59:47,918 --> 00:59:50,797
Her window's open
and there's a ledge running to it.

917
00:59:50,921 --> 00:59:52,389
A ledge? Ledge?

918
00:59:52,547 --> 00:59:55,346
More like a balcony.
Hold those.

919
01:00:09,314 --> 01:00:11,442
- Slow, slow, slow.
- I am going slow.

920
01:00:13,276 --> 01:00:15,574
- Don't look down.
- I'm not bloody looking down.

921
01:00:15,737 --> 01:00:17,785
Oh... Oh!

922
01:00:19,866 --> 01:00:21,288
Turn around, turn around.

923
01:00:21,451 --> 01:00:26,332
See? Turn around. There you go.
That's it. You're all right now.

924
01:00:26,498 --> 01:00:29,593
This is good. I got it.

925
01:00:32,087 --> 01:00:33,714
Well done. Well done.

926
01:00:33,880 --> 01:00:37,350
You're being very brave.
You're being very, very brave.

927
01:00:38,593 --> 01:00:40,391
- Oh!
- Oh!

928
01:00:41,721 --> 01:00:43,143
Oh, fuck!

929
01:00:43,306 --> 01:00:44,353
Wait, wait, wait.

930
01:00:44,516 --> 01:00:46,564
I've got you. I've got you.

931
01:00:48,937 --> 01:00:52,237
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

932
01:01:08,540 --> 01:01:11,259
- Cats.
- And flowers.

933
01:01:27,434 --> 01:01:29,653
The 19th century.

934
01:01:31,730 --> 01:01:34,404
I'm gonna get changed.

935
01:01:34,566 --> 01:01:35,943
<i>Excusez-moi.</i>

936
01:01:39,696 --> 01:01:41,448
Go with her.

937
01:02:12,437 --> 01:02:13,437
Ssh...

938
01:02:25,742 --> 01:02:27,369
I'm coming.

939
01:02:29,537 --> 01:02:32,507
Come in! Entrez!

940
01:02:53,228 --> 01:02:54,855
What?

941
01:02:55,021 --> 01:02:57,399
- You want to watch me get dressed now?
- Eh?

942
01:02:57,565 --> 01:02:59,533
Get out! Get out!

943
01:03:09,869 --> 01:03:12,247
She just... OK.

944
01:03:16,876 --> 01:03:18,253
Ssh!

945
01:03:20,880 --> 01:03:23,884
Oh, sorry. You're probably wondering
what I am doing.

946
01:03:24,050 --> 01:03:27,099
- It's not...
- I'm so glad you're here.

947
01:03:27,262 --> 01:03:28,434
Oh, there, there.

948
01:03:28,596 --> 01:03:33,477
Now, just sit down
and tell Auntie... Miriam all your worries.

949
01:03:33,685 --> 01:03:35,153
What's the matter?

950
01:03:35,312 --> 01:03:38,316
I've made a terrible mistake.

951
01:03:38,481 --> 01:03:42,076
He does not love me.
He never has and he never will.

952
01:03:42,235 --> 01:03:44,738
I've sold myself to the devil.

953
01:03:44,904 --> 01:03:49,000
- I'm a whore. I'm a devil's whore.
- No, no, you're not.

954
01:03:49,159 --> 01:03:52,003
- No, no, no.
- Yes, yes, yes.

955
01:03:52,162 --> 01:03:54,506
No, no, no, you're not.
Of course you're not.

956
01:03:54,622 --> 01:03:59,753
Yes, I am.
I'm a terrible, horrible, shallow person.

957
01:03:59,919 --> 01:04:02,342
I am a fake. I am a fake.

958
01:04:02,547 --> 01:04:05,801
I am a fake. I am a fake.

959
01:04:06,009 --> 01:04:07,370
No, don't say that about yourself.

960
01:04:07,510 --> 01:04:13,017
From what I can tell, you're a highly original,
slightly highly strung, bright, imaginative girl.

961
01:04:13,183 --> 01:04:14,480
- Really?
- Yes.

962
01:04:14,642 --> 01:04:16,940
- You really think so?
- I do. I do. Really.

963
01:04:17,103 --> 01:04:20,198
That is the nicest thing
anyone has ever said to me.

964
01:04:20,357 --> 01:04:24,487
Oh, no! Oh, thank you.
Thank you, you're so nice.

965
01:04:24,652 --> 01:04:26,132
No, I'm not, really.

966
01:04:31,993 --> 01:04:35,873
Please excuse me.
I'll be right back. Sorry.

967
01:04:36,039 --> 01:04:37,962
There, there, Manon.

968
01:04:39,376 --> 01:04:40,878
Why are you crying?

969
01:04:41,044 --> 01:04:44,890
- Me? Oh, it's the flowers. I'm, er... allergic.
- Oh! Oh, I'm so sorry.

970
01:04:45,048 --> 01:04:46,925
- It's all right.
- Oh.

971
01:04:47,092 --> 01:04:49,220
No, no, no, Manon.
It's fine, really.

972
01:04:49,386 --> 01:04:54,517
- No, don't do that.
- Bloody things! I don't like them anyway.

973
01:05:07,404 --> 01:05:09,202
- What would you do?
- Me?

974
01:05:09,364 --> 01:05:13,585
Yes. You're clearly a woman of the world.
What do you think of him?

975
01:05:13,785 --> 01:05:15,253
- Your husband?
- Yes.

976
01:05:15,412 --> 01:05:19,838
- Well, I mean, he's fine. He's...
- Fine?

977
01:05:20,041 --> 01:05:22,544
Actually, I think he's a bit callous.

978
01:05:22,710 --> 01:05:26,055
I'm sorry, I think you could do better.

979
01:05:26,214 --> 01:05:27,841
I think he probably...

980
01:05:28,007 --> 01:05:31,432
I think he probably treats you
like a piece of jewellery.

981
01:05:31,553 --> 01:05:33,100
I think he probably treats you badly.

982
01:05:33,221 --> 01:05:37,067
That's not to say he can't change.
I mean, they can change. People do change.

983
01:05:37,225 --> 01:05:42,573
But it's easy to say I love you while
you're rolling around on expensive sheets.

984
01:05:42,730 --> 01:05:46,200
It's so much harder
when they need washing.

985
01:05:49,404 --> 01:05:54,410
Look, I'm not who you think I am.
I'm sorry, I'm not Miriam from Weymouth.

986
01:05:54,534 --> 01:05:57,913
I'm not even Katie from Texas.
I'm just Kate from Surrey.

987
01:05:58,079 --> 01:06:00,800
And my ex-husband is lying on the floor
next to your bed, I'm afraid.

988
01:06:00,874 --> 01:06:02,547
- He is?
- Yep.

989
01:06:02,709 --> 01:06:05,212
Oh! Hello.

990
01:06:06,045 --> 01:06:08,468
- Hi.
- And why are you crying?

991
01:06:08,673 --> 01:06:11,142
The cats.
But don't throw them out the window.

992
01:06:11,301 --> 01:06:16,979
- Oh, he's really handsome.
- I know. It's irritating.

993
01:06:17,140 --> 01:06:19,689
- Not sure about the moustache.
- I agree.

994
01:06:19,851 --> 01:06:22,570
The thing is, you see,
your husband stole something from us

995
01:06:22,729 --> 01:06:24,330
and from a lot
of other very good people.

996
01:06:24,439 --> 01:06:27,568
Something very valuable to us:
our future.

997
01:06:27,734 --> 01:06:34,208
And so we came here tonight to take back
what we feel is rightfully ours.

998
01:06:34,365 --> 01:06:36,208
Oh. The diamond.

999
01:06:36,367 --> 01:06:39,712
<i>- It's not very imaginative,</i> I <i>grant you.
- Sorry, my back was killing me.</i>

1000
01:06:41,164 --> 01:06:45,715
- Manon, open up. It's Vincent.
- Take it. I don't like it anyway.

1001
01:06:45,877 --> 01:06:48,346
Great. Here's the fake.

1002
01:06:50,924 --> 01:06:52,221
Manon!

1003
01:06:53,927 --> 01:06:55,304
What?

1004
01:06:59,849 --> 01:07:01,647
Why are you throwing ﬂowers
out the window?

1005
01:07:01,809 --> 01:07:05,609
I'm allergic.
Don't you know anything about me?

1006
01:07:07,941 --> 01:07:12,367
You must take good care of this.
It's not a toy, it's very valuable.

1007
01:07:13,154 --> 01:07:15,202
More valuable than me?

1008
01:07:15,365 --> 01:07:21,418
Darling, there is nothing on earth that is
more valuable to me than me... than you!

1009
01:07:21,538 --> 01:07:23,540
You should know that.

1010
01:07:27,961 --> 01:07:32,307
And will you still love me
even when we are washing the sheets?

1011
01:07:40,306 --> 01:07:41,808
Ssh!

1012
01:07:45,812 --> 01:07:46,859
What are you doing?

1013
01:07:47,063 --> 01:07:48,815
I don't know.
I thought you were about to sneeze.

1014
01:07:48,982 --> 01:07:51,826
- Causing a distraction's supposed to stop it.
- That's hiccups.

1015
01:07:52,402 --> 01:07:54,450
<i>Ah...</i> yes.

1016
01:07:55,822 --> 01:07:58,041
I might sneeze again.

1017
01:08:03,746 --> 01:08:05,874
What are we doing?
We've got to get out of here.

1018
01:08:06,040 --> 01:08:07,792
Oh, OK.

1019
01:08:07,959 --> 01:08:09,836
- What, back the way we came?
- Yes!

1020
01:08:28,938 --> 01:08:32,909
- Oh! Sorry, old partner.
- Sorry, sorry.

1021
01:08:33,026 --> 01:08:34,152
Yeah, howdy.

1022
01:08:40,700 --> 01:08:45,422
Although not on the official schedule,
my new wife would like to say a few words.

1023
01:08:48,041 --> 01:08:54,014
A wise woman once told me
that you can love your husband

1024
01:08:54,172 --> 01:08:56,300
but you must also like him.

1025
01:08:59,927 --> 01:09:02,021
Wait, wait, wait, wait.

1026
01:09:02,180 --> 01:09:05,901
And I finally realised that...

1027
01:09:07,602 --> 01:09:12,654
...I don't love Vincent or even like him.

1028
01:09:15,318 --> 01:09:18,538
<i>So Vincent, darling...</i>

1029
01:09:20,198 --> 01:09:21,916
...I want a divorce.

1030
01:09:32,669 --> 01:09:37,391
Stop! Stop!
There's been a travesty of justice.

1031
01:09:39,592 --> 01:09:41,390
Catch them!

1032
01:09:41,552 --> 01:09:42,552
Catch them!

1033
01:09:44,514 --> 01:09:47,643
<i>Hey! Vive la révolution!</i>

1034
01:09:48,309 --> 01:09:50,277
<i>Vive la révolution!</i>

1035
01:09:51,312 --> 01:09:52,689
Oh!

1036
01:09:54,524 --> 01:09:57,243
- Oh, my God, no!
- No, no.

1037
01:10:07,120 --> 01:10:08,872
- Sorry, sorry-
- Sorry.

1038
01:10:09,580 --> 01:10:10,923
Ooh! Ow!

1039
01:10:11,040 --> 01:10:14,169
I knew there was something familiar
about you.

1040
01:10:14,585 --> 01:10:16,303
Ooh!

1041
01:10:16,462 --> 01:10:17,634
Ow!

1042
01:10:17,797 --> 01:10:19,174
Oh, no! They're real.

1043
01:10:19,966 --> 01:10:25,439
OK, let's make this simple.
Where is the real diamond?

1044
01:10:27,890 --> 01:10:30,268
Bloody hell.

1045
01:10:37,567 --> 01:10:40,116
- Oh!
- Oh, that's a whole other level of pain.

1046
01:10:40,278 --> 01:10:45,079
Look, we're just a disgruntled employee and
his pushy wife who want back what's theirs.

1047
01:10:45,241 --> 01:10:47,209
- You didn't say ex-wife.
- No, I didn't, did I?

1048
01:10:47,368 --> 01:10:49,086
- Mmm...
- We should focus.

1049
01:10:49,245 --> 01:10:51,498
- Right.
- Have you ever heard of karma?

1050
01:10:52,582 --> 01:10:55,461
Perhaps you're being punished
for all the bad things

1051
01:10:55,626 --> 01:10:58,379
that you might have done in your life.

1052
01:11:01,507 --> 01:11:03,134
It's just a thought.

1053
01:11:04,385 --> 01:11:07,685
Oh, no! That's just mean!
You're just being a bully now!

1054
01:11:07,847 --> 01:11:09,770
Be grateful, I don't hit women.

1055
01:11:10,725 --> 01:11:14,650
Now, tell me where my diamond is!

1056
01:11:30,620 --> 01:11:32,588
I swallowed it.

1057
01:11:33,790 --> 01:11:35,713
I sold the diamond.

1058
01:11:35,875 --> 01:11:37,047
What?

1059
01:11:37,210 --> 01:11:39,884
I swapped it and sold the real one.

1060
01:11:41,088 --> 01:11:45,810
Gave the money to charity,
an orphanage in Calcutta.

1061
01:11:45,968 --> 01:11:47,470
What? Why?

1062
01:11:47,637 --> 01:11:50,186
A test, to see if you really loved me.

1063
01:11:50,348 --> 01:11:53,101
You're crazy.
I'll deal with you later.

1064
01:11:53,267 --> 01:11:55,520
Get rid of them.

1065
01:11:56,270 --> 01:11:57,271
Oh, no.

1066
01:11:57,438 --> 01:11:59,782
<i>OK, er...</i>

1067
01:11:59,941 --> 01:12:02,319
If I'd known,
I'd have worn better underwear.

1068
01:12:02,527 --> 01:12:04,950
I don't think it's your underwear
you should be worrying about, Pen.

1069
01:12:05,112 --> 01:12:06,910
- These things reveal everything.
- What do you mean?

1070
01:12:07,073 --> 01:12:09,701
- Yeah, every nook and cranny.
- Oh, God!

1071
01:12:12,453 --> 01:12:14,000
What are you looking at?

1072
01:12:15,706 --> 01:12:18,255
Damn cheek!

1073
01:12:26,926 --> 01:12:28,644
Oh, yes, that's, er... Saigon,

1074
01:12:28,803 --> 01:12:32,148
Vietnam, 1964.

1075
01:12:32,306 --> 01:12:34,729
Took a bit of shrapnel, yeah.

1076
01:12:34,851 --> 01:12:38,196
Bloody hell, they left some forceps
in there. Look, the clamp's in there.

1077
01:12:39,021 --> 01:12:40,421
- I didn't know that.
- You can go.

1078
01:12:40,439 --> 01:12:41,565
Bloody Vietnam.

1079
01:12:43,359 --> 01:12:46,784
- Take them to the cliff.
- Huh? The cliff?

1080
01:12:46,946 --> 01:12:49,495
Whisky? A last drink?

1081
01:12:49,657 --> 01:12:52,001
Not my tipple.

1082
01:12:57,540 --> 01:13:00,510
- I do hope they'll be all right, Jerry.
- I'm sure they'll be fine, love.

1083
01:13:00,668 --> 01:13:02,045
- Do you think?
- Yeah.

1084
01:13:14,098 --> 01:13:16,567
Stop whistling, Richard.

1085
01:13:16,726 --> 01:13:19,696
- Please, stop whistling. It drives me mad.
- Helps me relax, Kate.

1086
01:13:19,854 --> 01:13:22,403
Well, it doesn't help me relax.
It's driving me bloody mad.

1087
01:13:22,565 --> 01:13:24,442
OK, I'll stop.
I've stopped whistling now, OK?

1088
01:13:39,832 --> 01:13:42,051
We've stopped.

1089
01:13:42,209 --> 01:13:43,631
Yes.

1090
01:13:50,301 --> 01:13:52,349
- We're moving.
- Yes.

1091
01:14:02,688 --> 01:14:04,565
- Kate.
- What?

1092
01:14:04,732 --> 01:14:06,575
- I just wanted to say...
- What?

1093
01:14:06,734 --> 01:14:08,828
I just wanted to say, Kate,
that whatever happens...

1094
01:14:08,945 --> 01:14:13,121
- You're not trying to do a final speech, are you?
- No, not at all. Well, maybe a little.

1095
01:14:17,078 --> 01:14:18,625
It's just that...

1096
01:14:18,788 --> 01:14:20,256
- Shut up!
- All right, I will.

1097
01:14:25,795 --> 01:14:26,921
Oh!

1098
01:14:27,922 --> 01:14:29,549
- Oh!
- Oh!

1099
01:14:32,426 --> 01:14:34,804
Don't... move.

1100
01:14:45,773 --> 01:14:47,901
- Oh.
- Ohh!

1101
01:14:48,067 --> 01:14:50,268
- What's going on?
- We're going back. We're going back!

1102
01:14:50,277 --> 01:14:52,871
- No, no, no, no, no.
- Ssh, ssh, ssh, ssh, ssh.

1103
01:14:52,989 --> 01:14:54,991
No, no, no, no.

1104
01:14:56,951 --> 01:14:58,999
I just wanted to say I'm sorry, Kate.

1105
01:14:59,161 --> 01:15:00,378
What for?

1106
01:15:00,538 --> 01:15:02,882
For not being a good husband.

1107
01:15:04,542 --> 01:15:05,919
I'm sorry too, then.

1108
01:15:06,085 --> 01:15:07,928
For what?

1109
01:15:08,129 --> 01:15:09,722
For not letting you be one.

1110
01:15:09,880 --> 01:15:11,507
What do you mean?

1111
01:15:11,674 --> 01:15:13,347
- We were too young.
- Uh-huh.

1112
01:15:13,509 --> 01:15:17,764
It takes two, you know, to totally
ruin a marriage, and I played my part.

1113
01:15:18,347 --> 01:15:19,564
Oh, God!

1114
01:15:19,682 --> 01:15:22,151
Anyway, what does it matter now?
We're...

1115
01:15:24,687 --> 01:15:25,813
We're going to die!

1116
01:15:29,191 --> 01:15:33,367
- Richard!
- It's OK. I've got you. Hold on.

1117
01:15:35,239 --> 01:15:37,958
Kate, I think we should try again.

1118
01:15:39,493 --> 01:15:41,962
- Try what again?
- Me and you.

1119
01:15:42,121 --> 01:15:44,044
What are you talking about, Richard?

1120
01:15:44,206 --> 01:15:46,584
I think we should finally sail round the
world, like we've always talked about.

1121
01:15:46,751 --> 01:15:48,753
I've had such a great time
these past few days.

1122
01:15:48,878 --> 01:15:52,303
Could you just concentrate?
Concentrate on holding on!

1123
01:15:52,465 --> 01:15:55,264
- Well, don't you feel anything, Kate?
- Yes, fear!

1124
01:15:55,426 --> 01:15:57,474
All right. OK.
Well, just think about it.

1125
01:15:59,513 --> 01:16:02,687
I like you, I really like you.

1126
01:16:08,522 --> 01:16:10,274
Come on, you fucker!

1127
01:16:11,734 --> 01:16:13,156
Come on!

1128
01:16:23,746 --> 01:16:24,963
- Are you OK?
- Manon!

1129
01:16:25,081 --> 01:16:28,927
- Manon!
- Oh! Oh, thank you. Thank you!

1130
01:16:29,085 --> 01:16:32,840
Oh, no, it is I who should be thanking you
for making me see things clearly.

1131
01:16:33,005 --> 01:16:34,257
<i>Merci beaucoup.</i>

1132
01:16:36,092 --> 01:16:38,015
We must go. Help me.

1133
01:16:39,011 --> 01:16:40,809
Here we go.

1134
01:16:57,279 --> 01:17:00,249
- Nice girl, passionate.
- Oh, I do hope she'll be all right.

1135
01:17:00,407 --> 01:17:02,580
Oh, a headstrong girl like her,
she'll be fine.

1136
01:17:03,244 --> 01:17:04,712
We're gonna have to swim out of here.
You know that?

1137
01:17:04,912 --> 01:17:08,257
- We'll be sitting ducks.
- Yeah, well, do you have a better idea?

1138
01:17:08,415 --> 01:17:09,758
I know a man with a boat.

1139
01:17:09,917 --> 01:17:10,917
<i>- You do'?
- Yeah.</i>

1140
01:17:17,758 --> 01:17:20,807
- Online?
- Yes, Richard, online.

1141
01:17:20,970 --> 01:17:26,272
You chat, you get to know each other, and you
agree to meet up, if you like each other.

1142
01:17:26,433 --> 01:17:28,561
- But you've never met him?
- No, not yet.

1143
01:17:28,727 --> 01:17:30,407
So you don't even know if you'll like him.

1144
01:17:30,437 --> 01:17:32,030
Well, he's 57. He lives in Paris

1145
01:17:32,148 --> 01:17:34,401
and has house and a boat
in the south of France. What's not to like?

1146
01:17:34,567 --> 01:17:37,491
Good heavens, Kate!
How shallow you've become.

1147
01:17:41,031 --> 01:17:43,250
That must be the captain.

1148
01:17:45,870 --> 01:17:49,750
Bonjour, Kate.
It's me, Jean-Baptiste.

1149
01:17:50,916 --> 01:17:52,634
Bloody hell!

1150
01:18:01,802 --> 01:18:03,850
You know, I'm twice your age.

1151
01:18:04,013 --> 01:18:06,937
What can I say? I like older women.

1152
01:18:07,099 --> 01:18:09,397
Why lie on your profile?

1153
01:18:09,560 --> 01:18:14,441
I want women to see me <i>as</i> a mature man.
Otherwise, I feel like a total cliche, you know?

1154
01:18:14,607 --> 01:18:20,080
Young, rich, handsome, with a speedboat...
So terribly predictable.

1155
01:18:23,115 --> 01:18:25,163
He's your lover?

1156
01:18:25,326 --> 01:18:27,044
Ex-lover.

1157
01:18:27,203 --> 01:18:29,171
But you still have some feelings for him?

1158
01:18:34,585 --> 01:18:36,053
I don't know.

1159
01:18:36,837 --> 01:18:38,965
It's not good to look back.

1160
01:18:40,174 --> 01:18:41,642
No, you're right.

1161
01:18:41,800 --> 01:18:44,019
- It can make you feel a bit sick.
- Oh.

1162
01:18:49,183 --> 01:18:50,685
Shall we head back?

1163
01:18:50,851 --> 01:18:53,320
- Well, actually...
- We are going out.

1164
01:18:53,479 --> 01:18:56,153
- Oh, really? Out?
- Yes, on a date.

1165
01:18:56,315 --> 01:18:58,864
- Well, not a date. Not...
- Yes, a date.

1166
01:18:59,026 --> 01:19:01,370
But what about the, er...

1167
01:19:01,528 --> 01:19:02,996
...diamond?

1168
01:19:03,155 --> 01:19:04,998
You can handle that, can't you?

1169
01:19:06,242 --> 01:19:08,870
Are you telling me
you don't want to see this through now?

1170
01:19:09,036 --> 01:19:13,257
No, I... Well, I think so.
I mean, can't you deal with it on your own?

1171
01:19:13,415 --> 01:19:15,213
I'll meet you at the rendezvous in Paris.

1172
01:19:16,752 --> 01:19:18,129
Right.

1173
01:19:18,254 --> 01:19:20,677
<i>Right,</i> I <i>see. Well...</i>

1174
01:19:20,839 --> 01:19:24,719
I suppose I did start all this for a reason
and the reason was for the...

1175
01:19:24,885 --> 01:19:27,263
...for the people, for...
for Doreen, for...

1176
01:19:30,015 --> 01:19:32,484
Right, I'll be off, then.

1177
01:19:32,643 --> 01:19:35,362
- You take good care of her.
- I will.

1178
01:19:42,778 --> 01:19:47,124
So, first of all,
we have some champagne at my villa.

1179
01:19:47,283 --> 01:19:50,287
OK. It's a bit early, isn't it,
for champagne?

1180
01:19:50,494 --> 01:19:53,464
It's never too early for champagne.
It's always too late.

1181
01:19:56,417 --> 01:19:57,794
Ah!

1182
01:19:58,002 --> 01:20:00,596
Oh, thank goodness. You made it.

1183
01:20:00,754 --> 01:20:01,846
Where's Kate?

1184
01:20:02,006 --> 01:20:04,429
Ah, she's not here.

1185
01:20:04,591 --> 01:20:05,968
Where is she?

1186
01:20:06,885 --> 01:20:08,432
- She's with a Frenchman.
- Oh!

1187
01:20:08,595 --> 01:20:11,849
- What Frenchman?
- Jean-Baptiste.

1188
01:20:12,016 --> 01:20:13,609
You knew about him?

1189
01:20:13,726 --> 01:20:15,945
Oh! Oh, right. Jean-Baptiste, yeah.

1190
01:20:16,103 --> 01:20:18,276
Did everybody know about the Frenchman
apart from me?

1191
01:20:18,439 --> 01:20:20,908
But why is she meeting him?
You're back together now.

1192
01:20:21,025 --> 01:20:23,244
No, Pen, we're not back together.

1193
01:20:23,402 --> 01:20:26,121
You seemed so happy
so we just went along with it.

1194
01:20:26,238 --> 01:20:28,411
I suppose it was a bit
of a long shot anyway.

1195
01:20:28,574 --> 01:20:31,748
Probably wouldn't have worked
second time around.

1196
01:20:31,910 --> 01:20:33,833
Exactly.

1197
01:20:33,996 --> 01:20:37,500
Anyway, the diamond.
Where is it?

1198
01:20:37,666 --> 01:20:39,885
- Ah, yeah.
- There's been a slight delay.

1199
01:20:40,044 --> 01:20:43,139
Yeah, but... Pen's got me
on the old prune juice.

1200
01:20:44,214 --> 01:20:45,682
Should get the bomb doors open.

1201
01:20:47,885 --> 01:20:49,808
Maybe? No, false alarm.

1202
01:21:15,788 --> 01:21:18,632
- Where are you going?
- Ah, good morning.

1203
01:21:18,791 --> 01:21:20,259
There is a robe on the chair.

1204
01:21:27,049 --> 01:21:30,929
- I'm so sorry about last night.
- Oh, Jean-Baptiste, it was lovely.

1205
01:21:31,095 --> 01:21:34,349
- Yeah, but I drunk too much and...
- It happens. You're young.

1206
01:21:34,973 --> 01:21:37,852
You've got much more experience than me.
That thing that you did...

1207
01:21:38,018 --> 01:21:40,191
Oh, thank you.

1208
01:21:40,354 --> 01:21:42,231
So, what would you like to do today?

1209
01:21:42,356 --> 01:21:44,404
We can have some breakfast outside or...

1210
01:21:44,608 --> 01:21:47,407
We can take my boat somewhere.
You can practise your French.

1211
01:21:49,279 --> 01:21:50,576
Ooh.

1212
01:21:51,490 --> 01:21:53,584
- You like this song?
- I love this song.

1213
01:21:53,742 --> 01:21:56,416
- Who is it?
- Free. You know...

1214
01:21:58,956 --> 01:22:00,754
No, I don't know this band.

1215
01:22:01,625 --> 01:22:04,754
No... of course you don't.

1216
01:22:09,007 --> 01:22:13,103
It was the linseeds that ultimately did it,
such a smooth transition.

1217
01:22:13,262 --> 01:22:14,639
- Well done, Jerry.
- Darling.

1218
01:22:14,805 --> 01:22:17,979
Amazing. Look at it.
It's beautiful. Touch it.

1219
01:22:18,142 --> 01:22:19,894
No, I think I'll pass, Jerry.

1220
01:22:20,686 --> 01:22:22,154
Thank you.

1221
01:22:22,312 --> 01:22:25,612
Where is this man, Diamond Dave?

1222
01:22:25,774 --> 01:22:27,902
Patience, my dear, patience.

1223
01:22:29,194 --> 01:22:31,037
- I'm sure she's coming, Richard.
- Mmm.

1224
01:22:31,196 --> 01:22:33,039
I don't think so, Pen.

1225
01:22:34,408 --> 01:22:35,751
Thanks, anyway.

1226
01:22:36,785 --> 01:22:40,665
I don't understand.
What is the Eye of the Rainbow?

1227
01:22:40,831 --> 01:22:43,459
It's a diamond that we stole.

1228
01:22:43,667 --> 01:22:49,049
But first we had to kidnap the Texans, scuba
to the chateau and break into a wedding.

1229
01:22:49,214 --> 01:22:51,763
- You stole a diamond?
- Yes.

1230
01:22:53,802 --> 01:22:56,430
- I'm not gonna make it.
- Yes, you will.

1231
01:23:06,482 --> 01:23:10,407
It's Diamond Dave.
He hasn't changed a bit.

1232
01:23:10,569 --> 01:23:13,493
- Don't take less than ten.
- Right you are.

1233
01:23:24,833 --> 01:23:27,507
- I just don't get it.
- What, my love?

1234
01:23:27,711 --> 01:23:29,759
How you know all these people?

1235
01:23:29,922 --> 01:23:32,345
- Who?
- Well, Diamond bloody Dave.

1236
01:23:32,508 --> 01:23:35,182
- Oh, you know, way back.
- No, I don't know, Jerry.

1237
01:23:35,344 --> 01:23:38,769
I don't know about Saigon
or Guam or the Foreign Legion.

1238
01:23:38,931 --> 01:23:42,435
- Or even Diamond bloody Dave. I really don't.
- It's all right. Calm down.

1239
01:23:42,601 --> 01:23:45,525
No, I won't calm down.
Who are these people, Jerry?

1240
01:23:45,687 --> 01:23:50,158
These contacts? All that metal
in your body? This past life?

1241
01:23:50,317 --> 01:23:52,661
I thought I knew you.
I thought we were the same.

1242
01:23:52,819 --> 01:23:54,913
Oh, Pen.

1243
01:23:58,659 --> 01:24:00,912
I'm more than the sum of my parts.

1244
01:24:01,745 --> 01:24:05,966
- What does that mean?
- I've got no idea.

1245
01:24:06,750 --> 01:24:10,550
But what I do know
is that I love you.

1246
01:24:10,712 --> 01:24:15,388
Always have, always will. OK?

1247
01:24:16,552 --> 01:24:19,271
- OK.
- Yeah!

1248
01:24:19,429 --> 01:24:22,399
- Got 15.
- Bloody hell.

1249
01:24:33,860 --> 01:24:36,158
You can literally go anywhere
from here, can't you?

1250
01:24:36,321 --> 01:24:38,790
Well, we've got a briefcase full of cash.

1251
01:24:40,158 --> 01:24:41,705
Penelope!

1252
01:24:41,868 --> 01:24:43,916
There's one back to London
in 50 minutes.

1253
01:24:46,248 --> 01:24:49,172
No, I don't think we should get that one.

1254
01:24:49,334 --> 01:24:51,132
- Kate!
- Hey-hey!

1255
01:24:53,797 --> 01:24:55,799
Listen, what do you think about...

1256
01:24:55,966 --> 01:24:59,345
I don't know, maybe doing a bit of
travelling before we head home?

1257
01:25:00,762 --> 01:25:01,762
Travelling?

1258
01:25:03,515 --> 01:25:06,689
- Well...
- Stupid idea, right?

1259
01:25:06,852 --> 01:25:08,320
Yes.

1260
01:25:09,313 --> 01:25:14,410
A crazy... daft... stupid...

1261
01:25:15,611 --> 01:25:17,864
but brilliant idea.

1262
01:25:18,030 --> 01:25:19,532
- Yeah?
- Yeah. Why the hell not?

1263
01:25:19,698 --> 01:25:22,417
- What have we got to lose?
- Apart from our dignity?

1264
01:25:22,576 --> 01:25:24,544
Either way, it's worth investigating.

1265
01:25:25,078 --> 01:25:27,957
Definitely. Let's investigate.

1266
01:25:29,416 --> 01:25:31,635
Would you see
that the relevant people get this?

1267
01:25:31,793 --> 01:25:32,919
It would be an honour, my friend.

1268
01:25:33,045 --> 01:25:36,094
I've, er... taken a bit out.
You can stash the rest under the mattress.

1269
01:25:36,256 --> 01:25:39,556
Don't worry, old pal. We've got a
safe house built under the stairs.

1270
01:25:39,718 --> 01:25:42,096
- We do?
- Yeah.

1271
01:25:44,181 --> 01:25:45,979
Bon <i>voyage,</i> my old friends.

1272
01:25:46,975 --> 01:25:48,773
- I'll feed the cat.
- Oh, thank you.

1273
01:25:48,935 --> 01:25:50,296
- Look after yourselves.
- We will.

1274
01:25:50,437 --> 01:25:51,484
Thank you.

1275
01:25:51,647 --> 01:25:54,116
- Come along, Jerry.
- Be very, very naughty.

1276
01:25:54,274 --> 01:25:56,777
- It's is very heavy, Jerry.
- Hey-hey!

1277
01:25:57,736 --> 01:25:59,864
- Come on, my love.
- I say...

1278
01:26:01,365 --> 01:26:02,992
Oh... yes.

1279
01:26:04,451 --> 01:26:05,919
<i>Merci.</i>

1280
01:26:08,789 --> 01:26:10,462
Come on.

1281
01:26:10,624 --> 01:26:11,921
Come on!

1282
01:26:24,262 --> 01:26:25,935
Oh, yew!

1283
01:26:26,098 --> 01:26:27,520
<i>Right. Yaw!</i>

1284
01:26:27,683 --> 01:26:29,026
Hey-hey-hey!

1285
01:26:54,668 --> 01:26:58,718
So, what next? Hmm?

1286
01:26:58,880 --> 01:27:00,848
A wander around the Marais?

1287
01:27:01,007 --> 01:27:03,385
Hmm, that would be nice.

1288
01:27:04,261 --> 01:27:09,392
But... I was thinking of something
a little more adventurous.

1289
01:27:09,558 --> 01:27:13,279
Adventurous? Marvellous.
When are we leaving?

1290
01:27:14,479 --> 01:27:16,607
What about right now?

1291
01:27:17,691 --> 01:27:19,318
OK?

1292
01:27:20,777 --> 01:27:22,905
<i>You</i> see, <i>I...</i>

1293
01:27:23,071 --> 01:27:26,701
I know a man.
I know a man with a boat.

1294
01:27:26,867 --> 01:27:28,414
- Oh, you do, do you?
- Yes.

1295
01:27:28,577 --> 01:27:30,625
Yes? What?

1296
01:27:31,621 --> 01:27:34,215
Where? No! This?

1297
01:27:34,374 --> 01:27:36,172
Oh, my God!
She's beautiful.

1298
01:27:36,334 --> 01:27:38,302
- Kate, you did it. You did it!
- I did it!

1299
01:27:38,462 --> 01:27:40,339
- You bought us a boat!
- I did it!

1300
01:27:40,505 --> 01:27:42,348
Don't fall in.
Don't fall in the Seine.

1301
01:27:42,507 --> 01:27:45,226
Oh, my God, she's gorgeous!

1302
01:27:45,385 --> 01:27:47,808
She is gorgeous.
You are gorgeous!

1303
01:27:48,013 --> 01:27:49,765
I love you!

1304
01:29:04,506 --> 01:29:08,511
"Mon Désarroi")

